3. **Molecular Cooling Threshold Analysis**: Compare the Sparkler GC mass distribution ($10^6 - 10^7 M_{\odot}$) against the theoretical halo mass threshold for molecular cooling ($M_{halo} \sim 10^5 - 10^6 M_{\odot}$) at $z \approx 2-4$. Account for the Lyman-Werner background sensitivity and the lower star-formation efficiency of these smaller halos to determine if Sparkler clusters represent the high-mass end of the cluster mass function within these environments.

